7 AS INTRODUCED
8 A Concurrent Resolution declaring May 14, 2025, as
the 9th annual Hispanic Cultural Day in Oklahoma;
9 recognizing the Hispanic community in Oklahoma; and
celebrating the heritage, culture, and contributions
10 of Hispanics to the State of Oklahoma.
11
12
13 WHEREAS, Hispanics are those who identify their origin as the
14 heritage, nationality group, lineage, or country of their birth or
15 that of their parents or ancestors before their arrival into the
16 United States; and
17 WHEREAS, Spanish-speaking countries include Argentina, Bolivia,
18 Chile, Colombia, Costa Rica, Cuba, Dominican Republic, Ecuador, El
19 Salvador, Guatemala, Honduras, México, Nicaragua, Panamá, Paraguay,
20 Perú, Spain, Uruguay, Venezuela, and the Commonwealth of Puerto
21 Rico; and
22 WHEREAS, Hispanics have been a part of the geography and history
23 of Oklahoma since the 16th Century when the Spanish initially
24 claimed Oklahoma, specifically the Oklahoma Panhandle; and
