1 WHEREAS, the first exploration of Oklahoma was led by the
2 Spaniard Francisco Vásquez de Coronado and his army in 1541 on their
3 journey to conquer the Seven Cities of Cíbola or Quivira, the area
4 known today as Cimarron County; and
5 WHEREAS, the majority of Oklahoma's Hispanic population live in
6 the cities of Oklahoma City, Tulsa, and Guymon; and
7 WHEREAS, Hispanics have migrated to the State of Oklahoma hoping
8 for better lives than the ones they left behind; and
9 WHEREAS, the influence of Hispanics in Oklahoma is a result of
10 their perseverance through hard times as well as their innate
11 yearning to establish a sense of place; and
12 WHEREAS, the median age of non-Hispanics in the United States is
13 fifty-four (54) years of age, the Hispanic median age is thirty (30)
14 years of age; and
15 WHEREAS, the economic impact of the Hispanic population in the
16 United States would rank as the fifth-largest economy in the world.
17 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
18 OF THE 1ST SESSION OF THE 60TH OKLAHOMA LEGISLATURE, THE SENATE
19 CONCURRING THEREIN:
20 THAT the Oklahoma House of Representatives and the Oklahoma
21 State Senate declare May 14, 2025, as the 9th annual Hispanic
22 Cultural Day in Oklahoma.
